    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I think that a scrollbar in each window would be a big UX win.\r\n\r\nI'm imagining the scrollbar as a single column, on the very right hand-side of each window, as is standard.\r\n\r\nThis could be very similar to the scrollbar in the insert completion popup menu. I don't care whether the \"gripper\" on the scrollbar is interactive or not (e.g. whether you can use the mouse to grab and move the scrollbar). The scrollbar could simply act as visual feedback, and I would be very happy.",
