        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "After https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/8455 is merged, this would be feasible for an alternative TUI (built with e.g. [libtickit](http://www.leonerd.org.uk/code/libtickit/) or [gocui](https://github.com/jroimartin/gocui))\r\n\r\n> The scrollbar could simply act as visual feedback, and I would be very happy.\r\n\r\nYou can get that in the statusbar via [vim-noscrollbar](https://github.com/gcavallanti/vim-noscrollbar) or [vim-line-no-indicator](https://github.com/drzel/vim-line-no-indicator)\r\n\r\nFor the standard builtin TUI this would cost 1 column per window, and it would cause extra redraws. PR would be accepted but not going to keep it as an open issue since it's likely to sit around for years.",
