            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I understand that this is not a priority right now.\r\n\r\nFor what it's worth, the scrollbar seems to already be possible in Oni, which not only shows the position of the window in the buffer, but also the position of the cursor in the window (I don't find this useful though).\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4657140/47111438-68863f80-d208-11e8-85e1-1b4fd4df9c95.png)\r\n\r\nI prefer terminal neovim, for now. I used to use vim-noscrollbar but it felt \"off\" because it is horizontal, and takes up too much space on my precious status line.\r\n\r\nvim-line-no-indicator looks nice since it is vertical, but I still think a \"standard\", full-length scrollbar would be nice in a TUI, whether it is the built-in one or an alternate.",
