            "body": ">PR would be accepted but not going to keep it as an open issue since it's likely to sit around for years.\n\nI think this is something worth supporting in the TUI, so we should re-open the issue and put it in the backlog/needs-owner milestone.\n\nA scrollbar is difficult (if not impossible) for a plugin to do well because it doesn't have the available primitives. @lewis6991's https://github.com/lewis6991/satellite.nvim (as well as the other plugins mentioned [earlier](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/9132#issuecomment-835195214)) works by making a 1~~px~~ cell wide floating window, which is clever (and works pretty well), but is a bit of a hack. Extmarks don't fully work since they are attached to a buffer line, which makes handling folds much more complicated and also makes it impossible to draw the scrollbar past the end of the buffer (nevertheless, I've made an [attempt](https://codeberg.org/gpanders/dotfiles/commit/2adbad927e1ff117d13670005782e64c0931224a)).\n\nbfredl mentioned that Vim supports this now, so we can look at importing those patches. Or maybe we can do our own from-scratch implementation.",
