        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">TUI scrollbar would be nice, but I assume it won't be able to support annotations/decorations as satellite does.\n\nI think an initial implementation (enough to close this issue) would indeed just be a dumb scrollbar, but longer term I can imagine the \"scrollcolumn\" being another column on the right side of the window that supports adding arbitrary signs/extmarks/annotations just like the sign column does (e.g. the user sets a decoration on a buffer line and indicates that it should appear in the \"scroll column\" and then Nvim does all of the calculations to determine where in the actual window that annotation should appear).",
